ba44d.textContent:
LncRNA-like NMRK2 binds to HSPE1 (Hsp10),
and stabilizes it.  This enhances the role of
HSPE1 in mitochondrial unfolded protein response
(mtUPR), which increases mitochondrial activity.

ce47c.textContent:
LncRNA-like NMRK2 mRNA binds to miRNAs and 
upregulates SLC19A2, a novel NAD+ transport that
localizes to mitochondrial membrane.

d7e90.textContent:
NONO-TFE3 fusion
protein upregulates
NMRK2 and MALAT1

ec0f3.textContent:
Proposed NONO-TFE3 tRCC treatment:
Inhibition of lncRNA like NMRK2 mRNA

edf4f.textContent:
GAS5 is a lncRNA that normally inhibits mitochrondrial 
respiration.  In NONO-TFE3 tRCC, lncRNA-like NMRK2 
mRNA binds to GAS5.  This blocks GAS5 inhibition, and
increases mitochondrial activity.

publicationXrefe8c.standardName: LncRNA like NMRK2 mRNA functions as a key molecular scaffold to enhance mitochondrial respiration of NONO-TFE3 rearranged renal cell carcinoma in an NAD(+) kinase-independent manner.

pathway.author: [Eweitz]

comments.content: NMRK2 mRNA acts as a long non-coding RNA (lncRNA) and enhancing mitochondrial respiration in NONO-TFE3 translocation renal cell carcinoma (tRCC).  NMRK2 functions as a molecular scaffold to promote mitochondrial function in these cancer cells, independent of NAD+ kinase activity.  NMRK2 upregulation contributes to tumor progression by improving cellular energy production through enhanced mitochondrial respiration. Targeting NMRK2 might help treat this aggressive RCC subtype.
